    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Though scientists understand little about how a vracinea’s paralyzing scent affects the brain, weapon designers across the galaxy have been inspired by its effects and have replicated them with custom hybrid grenades. When it bursts, a pheromone grenade deals no damage, instead dispersing a powerful cocktail of supercharged pheromones and magically modified mind-altering chemicals in the listed blast radius. Each creature in the radius that inhales the pheromones (which bypass even active @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.WP7hddXW4mLXXXOg]{Environmental protections} from a suit of armor) must attempt a Will saving throw. A creature that fails its save is @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.7PPRS6krnvaTHbxh]{Fascinated} for a number of rounds equal to the grenade’s mark number as they gaze in wonder at sparkling trails that only they can see. A creature that succeeds at its save is immune to the effects of pheromone grenades for 24 hours. This is a mind-affecting effect.</p>"
    },
